Diagnostic criteria for autoimmune pancreatitis. Autoimmune pancreatitis (AIP), a particular type of pancreatitis, is thought to have an autoimmune etiology it is recognized as a distinct entity worldwide. AIP has many characteristic clinical, serologic, morphologic, and histopathologic features. In the absence of a diagnostic serologic marker for AIP, AIP should be diagnosed on the basis of combination of characteristic findings. AIP responds dramatically to steroid therapy